As regards the effects of an epidemic on the overall economy – with a tradables sector (T) and a non-tradables sector (N) – a simple analytical starting point is the Mundell Structural Equilibrium Model which looks at the equilibrium conditions in the T market and the N market as well as the money market (money market equilibrium is portrayed in the MM curve:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
